ght on prewar Japan and confirms the opinions of those in Washington who advocated economic pressure against Japan. At a time of growing interest in U.S.-Japanese economic relations, this book will be stimulating and provocative reading for scholars and students of international relations and American and Asian history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 4aAsian Studies. 4aHistory. 4aMilitary History.  a20th century japanese history.  aAsia.  aAxis Powers.  aImperial Japan.  aamerican foreign policy in japan.  aamerican history in japan.  aamerican history.  aasian history.  aautarky.  aeagle against the sun.  aforeign relations with japan.  ahistory of japanese imperial army.  ahistory of the imperial army.  ainternational relations.  ainterwar asia.  ainterwar japan.  ajapan economic security.  ajapan in the 1900s.  ajapan prewar history.  ajapan's domestic economy.  ajapanese economic conditions.  ajapanese economic history.  ajapanese economic policy.  ajapanese expansion.  ajapanese foreign policy.  ajapanese history.  ajapanese imperialism.  ajapanese military history.  ajapanese national security.  ajapanese restoration.  ajapanese studies.  ajapanese wartime culture.  ajapanese wartime imperialism.  amanchuria and japan.  ameiji restoration.  aorigins of the pacific war.  apolitical science.  aprewar tokyo.  astudents of international relations.  athe american war with japan.  athe china incident.  athe origins of the second world war in asia and the pacific.  au.s-japanese economic relations.  aworld war ii history.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013z978311053615740uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978080146846940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780801468469423Coveruhtt